class Solution(object):
    def canBeEqual(self, s1, s2):
        """
        :type s1: str
        :type s2: str
        :rtype: bool
        """
        # Since the operation only allows swapping characters 2 indices apart,
        # the parity (odd or even position) of the characters must remain the same.
        # We count the occurrence of each character in odd and even positions separately.
        odd1, even1, odd2, even2 = {}, {}, {}, {}
        for i in range(4):
            if i % 2 == 0:  # Even index
                even1[s1[i]] = even1.get(s1[i], 0) + 1
                even2[s2[i]] = even2.get(s2[i], 0) + 1
            else:  # Odd index
                odd1[s1[i]] = odd1.get(s1[i], 0) + 1
                odd2[s2[i]] = odd2.get(s2[i], 0) + 1
        
        # For s1 and s2 to be equal, their odd and even positioned characters (after operations) must match.
        return odd1 == odd2 and even1 == even2
